olive oil
1 packet Mild Chorizo
1 onion
1 tomato
1 courgette
1 packet arborio rice
1 packet garlic paste
1 packet tomato paste
2 cup boiling water
40 g butter
1 packet salad leaves
1 sachet Nan's Special Seasoning
1 packet Grated Parmesan Cheese

• Preheat oven to 220°C/200°C fan-forced. Roughly chop mild chorizo and red onion.
• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium high heat. Cook chorizo and onion, stirring, until starting to brown, 3-4 minutes.
• Meanwhile, boil the kettle. Roughly chop tomato and courgette.
• Add tomato and courgette to chorizo and cook, tossing, until starting to soften, 3-4 minutes.

• Add arborio rice, garlic paste, tomato paste and Nan's special seasoning to the pan with chorizo and cook, stirring, until fragrant, 1 minute.
• Remove from heat, then add the boiling water (2 cups for 2 people / 4 cups for 4 people). Stir to combine, then transfer risotto mixture to a baking dish. Cover tightly with foil and bake until liquid is absorbed and rice is 'al dente', 24-28 minutes.

TIP: 'Al dente' rice is cooked through but still slightly firm in the centre.

• When the risotto is done, stir through the butter, salad leaves and 1/2 the
grated Parmesan cheese. Season to taste.

TIP: If the risotto looks dry, stir through a splash of water

• Divide chorizo and veggie risotto between bowls.
• Top with remaining Parmesan cheese to serve.